Package aa.test.selenium

Class AA03EditProjectTest

java.lang.Object
aa.test.utils.AASeleniumManager
aa.test.selenium.AA03EditProjectTest
@TestMethodOrder(org.junit.jupiter.api.MethodOrderer.DisplayName.class) public class AA03EditProjectTest extends AASeleniumManager
Test editing projects. It currently implements changing the name or changing the project type of the project. It handles both billable and non-billable projects, so it will be easy to add other fields to change.

    • editProject

      private void editProject(String projectName, String fieldName, String newValue)
       Feature: Test editing projects

 Scenario: Edit the project based on the parameters.
 Given the project with the `projectName` exists
 Then open the Edit project form
 And assert that the Edit project form was opened
 And assert the project name (the correct project is edited)
 And change the value of the field in the form
 And submit the changes
 And assert that the correct client-snackbar appeared
      Parameters:
      projectName - the name of the project to be edited
      fieldName - which form field will be edited
      newValue - the new value of the form field

    • clickSpecifyBillingDetails

      private void clickSpecifyBillingDetails()
       Feature: Test editing projects

 Scenario: If the edited project specified billing details, process it
 Given the Edit project form is opened
 And the fields in the first part are edited
 Then check if the project specifies billing details
 And check if the form behaves correctly in this matter
 And get the form to the point when the Save changes button is shown
      Parameters:
      projectName - the name of the project to be edited
      fieldName - which form field will be edited
      newValue - the new value of the form field
